README.md
     1→# `sqlite-vec`
     5→An extremely small, "fast enough" vector search SQLite extension that runs
     6→anywhere! A successor to [`sqlite-vss`](https://github.com/asg017/sqlite-vss)
     7→
     8→<!-- deno-fmt-ignore-start -->
     9→
    10→> [!IMPORTANT]
    11→> _`sqlite-vec` is a pre-v1, so expect breaking changes!_
    12→
    13→<!-- deno-fmt-ignore-end -->
    14→
    15→- Store and query float, int8, and binary vectors in `vec0` virtual tables
    16→- Written in pure C, no dependencies, runs anywhere SQLite runs
    17→  (Linux/MacOS/Windows, in the browser with WASM, Raspberry Pis, etc.)
    18→- Store non-vector data in metadata, auxiliary, or partition key columns
    19→
